fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Recall that a smooth 1-motive X over a scheme S consists of






    a group scheme L over S that, locally, for the étale topology, is a constant group scheme defined by a free \mathbb {Z}-module of finite type;
    an abelian scheme A over S, and a torus T over S;





    an extension E of A by T, and a morphism \bar {u} \colon  L \to  A;





    a morphism u \colon  L \to  E lifting \bar {u}.

